# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Private / internal documents (session transcripts, planning notes,
# personal scripts, handoff docs). Kept locally for reference but
# never pushed to the public repo.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
docs/private/

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Third-party data sources — NOT shipped with the open-source code
# to respect copyright. Users supply their own data (see README).
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Data-fetch templates + fetched data (format-specific to Capital IQ
# or any equivalent data provider; user supplies their own)
knowledge_base/ciq_fetches/
TEST_DATA/

# Third-party screener exports — NEVER commit, regardless of folder.
# Users run their own screener and drop files into the designated
# folder per the DB integration plan; the raw files stay local.
US_CN_HK_dataset/
markets_dataset/
ginzu_cc_*.xls
ginzu_cc_*.xlsx

# Admin-built local database (derived from raw screener files via the
# admin refresh endpoint). Contains operator's upload manifest in
# ingest_log — kept local-only. The scrubbed distribution form lives
# at backend/data/valuation_seed.sqlite (COMMITTED to the repo).
backend/data_sources/*.sqlite
backend/data_sources/*.sqlite-journal
backend/data_sources/*.sqlite-wal
backend/data_sources/*.sqlite-shm

# (backend/data/valuation_seed.sqlite is explicitly NOT gitignored —
#  it's the public seed that clones load on first run.)

# Aswath Damodaran's reference workbooks and datasets — SHIPPED with
# the repo so clone-and-run works out of the box. Sourced from
# pages.stern.nyu.edu/~adamodar/ (publicly available for research use).
# If you want to use a fresher snapshot, replace these files from the
# Admin → Data Sources page.
# knowledge_base/Ginzu_NVIDIA.xlsx       (shipped — reference workbook)
# knowledge_base/damodaran/              (shipped — industry + macro data)
# knowledge_base/industry_lookup/        (shipped — ticker→industry map)

# Ginzu-understanding copies of prefilled workbooks
TEST_DATA/ginzu_prefilled/

